{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Political_Move",
  "title": "A Political Move",
  "summary": "At the military starport of New Alderaan on Ord Mantell, New Republic officer Rasi Praddhan Cen meets Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard and her spirited ten-year-old daughter Gabi to send them off aboard a captured smuggler's shuttle bound for Caspar, piloted by the gruff Navy veteran Mr. Stone. Once underway and Gabi safely occupied in the cockpit, Rasi briefs Ambrosia on her mission: the Empire intends to accuse the Caspian Democratic Union of secretly arming the Republic in order to justify seizing the Union's territory, and Ambrosia must bolster Caspian resolve through diplomacy and propaganda without driving the people to blame the Republic. He hands her a datapad of the Empire's documented evils, but Ambrosia -- a former slave herself, as her old throat scar attests -- flatly refuses to use exaggerations, insisting only the truth will do. She shares her knowledge of the Sarian people and their robust independence, and the two part with Rasi promising final instructions to the pilot while urging the weary ambassador to rest before the trials of Caspar.",
